You are iterating over the wrong indices. Java indices start at 0, so a String of `length()` characters has indices from `0` to `length()-1`.

Your loop should be 

    for(int i=0;i&lt;s.length();i++)

     for(int i=1;i&lt;=s.length();i++)

You have to delete the &quot;equals&quot;. That is why it is throwing an exception, you are simply going out of bounds of the string.
So the for loop should be `for(int i=0;i&lt;s.length();i++)`

Java Index starts from 0, so String size will never be more that length-1. So while looping use

    for(int i=0;i&lt;s.length();i++)  
or

    for(int i=1;i&lt;s.length()-1;i++)

